com.vector.cfg.gen.core.genusage.groovy.api

Interface IGenerationApi


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public interface IGenerationApi
    IGenerationApi is the entry point to the generation APIs and provide functionality for the generation process.

    (c) Copyright Vctr Informatik GmbH. All Rights Reserved.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      EGenerationProcessResult generate()
      Starts the generation.
      The last Settings block is used for generation or if no Settings block has been defined the standard project settings from the project file are used.
      EGenerationProcessResult generate(IGenerationSettingsApi settings)
      Starts the generation.
      This method takes a settings object as an argument.
      So it is possible to reuse a settings object.
      IGenerationSettingsApi getSettings()
      Returns the recently created settings object.
      IGenerationSettingsApi settings(groovy.lang.Closure<?> code)
      Opens an empty settings block.
      IGenerationSettingsApi settingsFromProject(groovy.lang.Closure<?> code)
      Opens a settings block which already pre configured with the project settings from the dpa file.
      EGenerationProcessResult validate()
      Starts the validation.
      The last Settings block is used for generation or if no Settings block has been defined the standard project settings from the project file are used.
